{"id": "1414364333726765056", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "81102419781492736", "author_name": "verz", "author_bot": false, "content": "As mentioned in the style guide, it says we want to use simple present tense for the majority of the work, unless they're flashbacks. So:\n\n- In the special ops category, are these events also to be considered in the present tense? Right now I've been going through the text and bringing it to the present tense as the AI created some inconsistencies but I was wondering if - within the frame of the event - we're to always treat them as past tense and use only present tense for main story.\n\n- In regards to italics: Obviously we don't wanna use it for audio descriptions, but is it appropriate to use it to emphasise a word stressed in a sentence?  For example:\n\n\"Rest assured, Miss Sophia, we are quite experienced in such matters.\" \nvs\n\"Rest assured, Miss Sophia, we are *quite* experienced in such matters.\"\n\nThey read differently in our minds! (Or at least to me anyways), so I was wondering our thoughts on that :)\n\nCheers! <:murphy_cake:1408324295180030002>", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T21:38:54.779000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1414365267135430687", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "I'm working on Horla's story, and I've been using italics that way. <:shrug:1003188954218123314> it just feels good sometimes", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T21:42:37.321000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414365717280587878", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "81102419781492736", "author_name": "verz", "author_bot": false, "content": "I'm glad someone else is <:noted:1408408581556015265>  it definitely helpls in places", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T21:44:24.644000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414375706833588317", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "836149624719802369", "author_name": "larvani", "author_bot": false, "content": "I think italics should be used as sparingly as possible, else it feels like you're relying on fonts instead of the writing to convey emotions", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T22:24:06.339000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414376571342553150", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "I disagree, proper use of italics *is* writing and does help to emphasize emotions, imo.", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T22:27:32.454000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414385601544716309", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 19, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "fully agree with this", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:03:25.422000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["836149624719802369"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1414375706833588317", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414385635393011712", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "italics are fine but they need to be reserved for very special occasions", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:03:33.492000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414385681140158515", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "Okie", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:03:44.399000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414385700622696520", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "emphasis loses its power the more you use it", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:03:49.044000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414386038641655851", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "but yes, effective use of italics is super strong and it's definitely a good idea for like, climactic scenes and major emotional passages", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:05:09.634000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414386156329504899", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "it's just that we need to be careful with how we use it because otherwise it ends up seeming trite and shallow if we use too much of it", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:05:37.693000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414387196055785583", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "81102419781492736", "author_name": "verz", "author_bot": false, "content": "That seems about right to me, I wouldn't want to use it too much but a good use of italics really does hit", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:09:45.583000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414387456635048036", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "81102419781492736", "author_name": "verz", "author_bot": false, "content": "Re: the tense stuff, are we wanting the side events to be written in present tense (unless a flashback ofc) ?", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:10:47.710000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414387800542937199", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "tenses are really hard to work with (I still have difficulty keeping my tenses consistent when translating/editing even after all these years <:auritacry:1396906080516440278>)", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:12:09.704000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414387909884379287", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "personally I have just been making my own judgements depending on the context - i.e., I'll use past tense if it's an obvious flashback, present tense for current scenes, etc", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:12:35.773000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "RosThumbsUp", "emoji_id": "1002223944738287626", "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1414388020735508500", "channel_id": "1414364333726765056", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "I think the only really important thing is probably to make sure you don't mix tenses within the same scene, but that's just my view on it", "timestamp": "2025-09-07T23:13:02.202000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1414364333726765056", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Tense & use of italics", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1410391772894330961", "1412867280844357813"]}
